args:
The hospitality face-off begins with a warm-up
bout, and Ieyasu's attendant Sazanka is
victorious over Botan in a war of soba noodles.
The next competition is a mock battle with
Ieyasu where the winner will receive
New Year's gifts known as an ＂otoshidama.＂
I have been around for a very long time,\nand yet this is a first even for my eyes!

I have seen this room a thousand times,
and yet with these decorations in place,
I would swear that I had entered the
great hall of some other nation.
I am delighted that it pleases you.
Please eat quickly before they grow soggy.
Oh man, these smell better'n hot bread\non a cold morning! This must be some\nkinda Hinomotoan specialty, yeah?
Indeed they are. And while we eat them\nat many times of the year, those served\nat New Year have extra significance.
In that case, I'm gonna shove noodles\ndown my gullet till I puk—
I ALSO MADE SOBA NOODLES,\nFOR THEY ARE ALSO MY SPECIALTY!
So drop those zero noodles and get\nwith my HERO noodles!
Is it my imagination, or is your soba\nabsorbing all of the broth?
Th-that's how it's supposed to be!\nMine are just awesome like that.
Well then, maybe we should call this the\nwarm-up round of our hospitality face-off.\nIt's a soba skirmish! A noodle knock-down!
I accept this challenge, for my noodles\nwill bring naught but glory unto the name\nof Master Ieyasu.
Sounds like it's time for a taste-test.
NOODLE TIME! I'll start with Sazanka's.
Oh dear. You appear to be shaking.\nHave my noodles given offense somehow?
They're so delicate—and yet the flavor\nis so complex!
Well, I was quite careful with the stock.\nStill, it pleases me to see you enjoy my\nhumble dish so.
Yeah yeah, it's a transcendent experience,\nblah blah blah. Try mine already!
Right! Lemme just pick yours up here\nand see how...it... Muh?
S-such an aggressive flavor...\n*cough* *hack* *wheeze*\nW-water! Water! Bring a bucket!
This soba's soggy as hell. Did you even\ntaste it before you slopped it down?
How dare you, sir?! You have besmirched\nmy name with your wild accusation!
But if it makes you happy... *nibble*\nHURRRGH! SO SALTY!
Have you selected a winner yet,\n{player_name}?
Well, they're both good...in their own way.
Oh, and on a related note, we'll all be\nhaving seconds of the winning soba!
Ulp! ...Er, I'm sorry, Botan, but I have to\ngive this one to Sazanka.
That's my darling! I always believed in you!
Pretty obvious if you ask me.
Yeah, okay. You may have won the\nwarm-up, but New Year's doesn't even\nstart until tomorrow—so get ready!
That reminds me—what are we actually\nDOING on New Year's?
We shall eat osechi in this room and\ndemonstrate traditional games of the\nholiday season.

A traditional meal eaten in Hinomoto
at New Year. It is made of various
ingredients, each with their own
intrinsic meaning.
For example, shrimp are for longevity,\nherring roe is for prosperous offspring,\nand so forth.
Absolutely fascinating. I would love to\nhear more about Hinomoto.
In that case, I think you will find\nour concept of ＂otoshidama＂ interesting.
The term originally referred to receiving\nthe good fortune shared by Amaterasu.
However, it now refers to a more tangible\ngift given with the goal of making the\nrecipient happy.
And lucky for you, we just happened to\nbring a few of those New Year's gifts\nwith us!
Of course. We want you all to enjoy the\nHinomotoan New Year's celebrations,\nafter all.

Also, both the shogun and Amaterasu have
commanded that we impart a sense of fun
when giving these gifts, so I must make
certain we can fulfill that obligation.
Thank you, Ieyasu. I'm sure you will.
To that end, you must battle me!
We must battle—for a gift handed over is\nnot nearly as fun as one that is earned!
Now then! If you defeat me in a contest\nof martial arts, I will give you your gifts.\nThis will be fun, no?
Aw, come on! I gotta EARN my present?
I mean, he's an expert even by\nHinomotoan standards, so I won't\nblame you for being a little chicken.
So yeah, maybe just give up now—\neven though you'll miss out on your\nchance to eat osechi.
Cram it, pal! I'm gonna fight for this gift,\nand I'm gonna WIN!
And I'll show you what a sylvan archer\nis capable of when there's loot involved!
And what exactly will you do,\n{player_name}?
Addis speaks with his usual swagger,\nbut it really is just a game. Just some\nlight sparring.
I am. At the very least, I'd like a chance\nto see what Hinomotoan martial arts\nare all about.
I'm in, too! Oh, but I'm gonna fight with\n{player_name}.
Huh? Why are you joining us?
Because I don't wanna lose to Ieyasu!\nThat means I'm kinda with you guys by\ndefault, right?
It matters not; I've trained my whole life to\nfight off superior numbers.
See? He's fine with it, I'm fine with it,\neverybody's fine with it. Now let's GO!
Well, I suppose it's all right.
Oh yeah! We're gonna have victory for\nDAYS up in this joint!
Let us move to an open area, then.\nIt wouldn't do to cause damage to\nthis lovely castle.
Bring it on, pal! We're gonna wipe the\nfloor with ya and then take some sweet,\nsweet New Year's giftage!
(Is it really okay that I agreed\nto do this...?)
